custom_steps_separated.content:
WHEN cacheing is turned on (note: this is on by default in the MLB app)

iOS appConfig.json Overide:

{
"midfield": {
"persistedQueries": true,
"getRequests": true}
}

Android Firebase config:
enable_midfield_persisted_queries : true
enable_midfield_get_requests : true

AND a midfield calls are initiated

custom_steps_separated.expected:
THEN the midfield calls will be GETs not POSTs
AND persistentQuery will be seen in the extensions query param, ex:

&extensions=%7B%22persistedQuery%22:%7B%22sha256Hash%22:%223948d87232c3956b31d3b4edca2c8948410d5a7a20e37eed9dc901ee8e892756%22,%22version%22:1%7D%7D&id=3948d87232c3956b31d3b4edca2c8948410d5a7a20e37eed9dc901ee8e892756 

AND for iOS 304 responses will be observed when the cache is missed

AND for Android 200 responses will be observed with the following payload when the cache is missed:
{
	"errors": [{
		"message": "PersistedQueryNotFound",
		"extensions": {
			"code": "PERSISTED_QUERY_NOT_FOUND"
		}
	}]
}

